column12: Inductions involved treating cells with 0.1% DMSO, as a vehicle control, or 10nM E2 (Sigma-Aldrich) for 1 hour.
column13: Ishikawa cells (Sigma-Aldrich) were grown in full media (RPMI-1640 (Gibco), 10% fetal bovine serum (Gibco), and 1% penicillin-streptomycin (Gibco)).  Five days prior to induction, cells were moved to hormone-depleted media with phenol-red free RPMI-1640(Gibco), 10% charcoal-dextran treated fetal bovine serum (Sigma-Aldrich), and 1% penicillin-streptomycin(Gibco).
